p: Compounds 181d (IC 50: D6 = 2610 ng/mL − W2 = 1280 ng/mL) and 181e (IC 50: D6 = >10,000 ng/mL − W2 = >10,000 ng/mL) also showed some activity decrease in both cones. The authors affirmed that this was related to the group present at C-7 because when this group was a ketone group (compound 181e) it was observed to be inactive.
